  Dialogue:
  - Why me?
  - I've never stolen, I've always been an honest politician, I've always thought
    of Sarka's good.
  - Why did you choose me as a victim?
  - Because you voted for a law that prohibited newspapers from publishing unpatriotic
    news.
  - I voted against this law!
  - Oh, sorry I got mixed up, your name is Romeu Hatter right?
  - "Romeu\u2026 you had voted in favor of which law?"
  - "I remembered, you voted for the law that banned the song \u201CLuna was right\u201D."
  - I didn't know laws could be so specific as to quote a particular song.
  - Are you serious? Sarka's parliament is totally rotten, truly absurd laws have
    already been passed here, laws that really destroyed this country, and I haven't
    even started talking about all the corruption there is.
  - And you're going to kill me because of such a ridiculous law? I just followed
    the party line when voting, I don't care one bit what the bards are singing.
  - Politicians are really good at speeches, even in the face of death you managed
    to come up with good arguments that almost made me change my mind.
  - But you are ignoring something.
  - I chose you precisely because you didn't do anything too serious.
  - 'As Adams would say:'
  - "\u201CTrue freedom is only obtained when we defend the right to practice the
    futile and immoral\u201D."
  - If a politician suffers a brutal punishment for attacking a small freedom, imagine
    the fear other politicians will have in attacking really important freedoms.
  - "You can not\u2026"
  - William covered the politician's mouth and drew his dagger.
  - Be silent, we've talked enough.
  - You're really good at arguing and persuading, but it's not politicians who rule
    this world.
  - Who rules this world is who is willing to use violence against those who go against
    their will.
  - That is the true law of this world.
  DialogueBR:
  - Por que justo eu?
  - "E nunca roubei, sempre fui um pol\xEDtico honesto, sempre pensei no bem de Sarka."
  - "Por que voc\xEA me escolheu como v\xEDtima?"
  - "Porque voc\xEA votou a favor de uma lei que proibia jornais de publicarem not\xEDcias
    anti patri\xF3ticas."
  - Eu votei contra essa lei!
  - "Oh, desculpe, eu me confundi, seu nome \xE9 Romeu Hatter certo?"
  - "Romeu\u2026 voc\xEA tinha votado a favor de qual lei mesmo?"
  - "Lembrei,  voc\xEA votou a favor da lei que proibia a m\xFAsica \u201CLuna estava
    certa\u201D. "
  - "Eu n\xE3o sabia que as leis podiam ser t\xE3o espec\xEDficas a ponto de citarem
    uma m\xFAsica em particular."
  - "Voc\xEA est\xE1 falando s\xE9rio? O parlamento de Sarka \xE9 totalmente podre,
    leis verdadeiramente absurdas j\xE1 foram aprovadas aqui, leis que realmente
    destru\xEDram este pa\xEDs, e eu nem comecei a falar de toda a corrup\xE7\xE3o
    que existe."
  - "E voc\xEA vai me matar por conta de uma lei rid\xEDcula dessas? Eu s\xF3 segui
    a orienta\xE7\xE3o partid\xE1ria ao votar, n\xE3o me interessa nem um pouco o
    que os bardos est\xE3o cantando."
  - "Pol\xEDticos s\xE3o realmente bons em discursar, mesmo diante da morte voc\xEA
    conseguiu elaborar bons argumentos que quase me fizeram mudar de ideia."
  - "Por\xE9m voc\xEA est\xE1 ignorando algo."
  - "Eu escolhi voc\xEA justamente porque voc\xEA n\xE3o fez nada muito grave."
  - 'Como diria Adams:'
  - "\u201CA verdadeira liberdade s\xF3 \xE9 obtida quando defendemos o direito de
    praticar o f\xFAtil e o imoral\u201D."
  - "Se um pol\xEDtico sofre uma puni\xE7\xE3o brutal por atacar uma liberdade pequena,
    imagine o medo que os outros pol\xEDticos ter\xE3o em atacar as liberdades realmente
    importantes."
  - "Voc\xEA n\xE3o pode\u2026"
  - "William tampou a boca do pol\xEDtico e sacou sua adaga."
  - "Sil\xEAncio, n\xF3s j\xE1 conversamos bastante."
  - "Voc\xEA \xE9 muito bom em argumentar e persuadir, mas n\xE3o s\xE3o os pol\xEDticos
    que governam este mundo."
  - "Quem governa este mundo \xE9 quem est\xE1 disposto a usar a viol\xEAncia contra
    aqueles que v\xE3o contra a sua vontade."
  - "Essa \xE9 a verdadeira lei deste mundo."
